# Environment Variables - Complete Setup Guide

This file documents ALL environment variables needed for the JTS Beauty ecommerce application (frontend + backend).

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
.env                              # Root - not typically used
.env.example                      # This file - template for all variables
.env.production                   # Production-specific (create before deploy)
.env.b4a                          # Back4App backend config
.env.hosting                      # Hosting.com backend config
server/.env                       # Backend runtime variables
frontend/.env.production          # Frontend production build variables
frontend/.env.production.example  # Frontend template
```

---

## 🔧 Quick Setup

### For Development
```bash
# 1. Copy templates
cp server/.env.example server/.env
# (No frontend .env needed for dev - uses defaults)

# 2. Edit with your values
nano server/.env

# 3. Start development
npm run dev              # Frontend dev server
npm --prefix server start   # Backend
```

### For Back4App Backend (Current Production)
```bash
# 1. Copy template
cp .env.b4a .env.production

# 2. Frontend build for Back4App
npm run build:b4a
# OR
npm run build   # Default uses Back4App URL
```

### For Hosting.com Deployment (New)
```bash
# 1. Copy template
cp .env.hosting .env.production

# 2. Edit with your domain
nano .env.production
# Replace: YOURDOMAIN → your-actual-domain

# 3. Frontend build for Hosting.com
source .env.hosting
npm run build
```

---

## 📝 Backend Environment Variables

### File: `server/.env`

```bash
# ============================================
# SERVER CONFIGURATION
# ============================================

# Port to listen on
# Default: 5000
PORT=5000

# Environment mode
# Options: development, production
# Default: development
NODE_ENV=production

# ============================================
# DATABASE - MongoDB Atlas
# ============================================

# MongoDB Atlas connection string
# Format: mongodb+srv://username:password@host/?appName=...
# REQUIRED: Server will not start without this
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://msaadali004_db_user:5thapril@cluster0.w2ymfcc.mongodb.net/?appName=Cluster0

# ============================================
# AUTHENTICATION - JWT
# ============================================

# JWT secret for signing tokens
# CRITICAL: Change to a strong, random value in production
# Recommendation: Use at least 32 random characters
# Generate: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# REQUIRED: Server will not start without this
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_this_in_production_to_something_very_secure_and_random_min_32_chars

# ============================================
# FRONTEND URLS - CORS Configuration
# ============================================

# Frontend URL for CORS whitelist
# This must match the domain where frontend is hosted
# For Hosting.com: https://yourdomain.hosting.com
# For GitHub Pages: https://saadsheikh5.github.io/ecoms
# For localhost: http://localhost:3000
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.hosting.com

# Alternative frontend URL (alias for CORS)
# Usually same as FRONTEND_URL
CLIENT_URL=https://yourdomain.hosting.com

# ============================================
# STRIPE - Payment Processing
# ============================================

# Stripe Secret API Key
# Get from: Stripe Dashboard → Developers → API Keys
# Format: sk_live_... (live) or sk_test_... (test)
# Optional in dev, REQUIRED for payments
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Stripe Webhook Signing Secret
# Get from: Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks
# Format: whsec_...
# REQUIRED for payment webhooks
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_1xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ============================================
# RATE LIMITING
# ============================================

# General API rate limit window (milliseconds)
# Default: 600000 (10 minutes)
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=600000

# Maximum requests per window for general API
# Default: 2000 (production), 1000 (development)
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=2000

# Login attempts rate limit window (milliseconds)
# Default: 900000 (15 minutes)
LOGIN_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000

# Maximum login attempts per window
# Default: 10 (production), 100 (development)
LOGIN_RATE_LIMIT_MAX=10

# ============================================
# EMAIL - Password Reset & Notifications (Optional)
# ============================================

# Email service provider
# Options: gmail, sendgrid, mailgun, etc.
EMAIL_SERVICE=gmail

# Email account username/address
EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com

# Email account password or app password
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Advanced Configuration
# ============================================

# Log level (not enforced by default)
# Options: error, warn, info, debug
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# Database pool size (not enforced by default)
# DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=10

# Cache TTL in seconds (not enforced by default)
# CACHE_TTL=3600
```

---

## 📦 Frontend Environment Variables

### File: `frontend/.env.production`

```bash
# ============================================
# FRONTEND PRODUCTION BUILD CONFIG
# ============================================

# API Base URL
# Can be relative path or absolute URL
# If relative: requests go to same domain (proxy required)
# If absolute: requests go directly to API endpoint
# Default (if not set): Uses build script's hardcoded URL
# Note: Current build script uses environment variable from scripts/build-pages.mjs
VITE_API_URL=/api

# API request timeout in milliseconds
# Default: 10000 (10 seconds)
VITE_API_TIMEOUT_MS=10000
```

**Note:** The frontend build script currently overrides this with `process.env.VITE_API_URL` from build context.

